request (client) → TLS encrypt/transport → server → tamper-evident log → verify/analyze → insider tamper → verify detects

Vertical Slice Flow

1.Client sends a TLS-encrypted request

2.Server receives request and records events using tamper-evident hash-chained logging

3.Logs are stored in binary format (tamperlog.bin, prev_hash.bin)

4.read_logs displays human-readable entries

5.verify_log recomputes the entire hash-chain to validate integrity

6.insider tampers with message bytes

7.verify_log detects the breach
